From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 03 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] linux-dmabuf: skip PRIME import check when driver doesn't support it

pvrsrvkm (PowerVR DDK 24.x) does not implement DRM_IOCTL_PRIME_FD_TO_HANDLE,
so drmPrimeFDToHandle() returns EINVAL.  wlroots treats this as a hard failure,
posts a Wayland protocol error to the client (EmulationStation), and ES
disconnects before it can display anything.

When the DRM device returns EINVAL or ENOSYS, the driver simply doesn't support
the PRIME FD→handle import path.  Fall through and let EGL decide at
eglCreateImageKHR time whether it can actually use the buffer — that is the
authoritative import check anyway.

---
 types/wlr_linux_dmabuf_v1.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/types/wlr_linux_dmabuf_v1.c b/types/wlr_linux_dmabuf_v1.c
index 5555555..6666666 100644
--- a/types/wlr_linux_dmabuf_v1.c
+++ b/types/wlr_linux_dmabuf_v1.c
@@ -215,6 +215,13 @@ static bool check_import_dmabuf(struct wlr_dmabuf_attributes *attribs, void *da
 	for (int i = 0; i < attribs->n_planes; i++) {
 		uint32_t handle = 0;
 		if (drmPrimeFDToHandle(linux_dmabuf->main_device_fd, attribs->fd[i], &handle) != 0) {
+			if (errno == EINVAL || errno == ENOSYS) {
+				// Driver doesn't support PRIME FD→handle import (e.g. pvrsrvkm).
+				// Skip the check and let EGL decide at import time.
+				wlr_log(WLR_DEBUG, "DRM device doesn't support PRIME FD import check, skipping");
+				return true;
+			}
 			wlr_log_errno(WLR_ERROR, "Failed to import DMA-BUF FD for plane %d", i);
 			return false;
 		}
